        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 8:08PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 808 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Penrose, or 16 miles northwest of Pueblo, moving
southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pueblo, Pueblo West, Pueblo Reservoir, and Penrose.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
central and southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
